Hospital Administrator - Aga Khan Health Service
Karachi
The incumbent will be responsible for overall administration of the unit by ensuring provision of quality of health care services to patients. S/he will also be responsible for planning, organising, directing and monitoring day to day operational activities. S/he will be required to develop business plan, execute and monitor financial policies and procedures set by the organisation.
Candidate should be MBBS preferably with masterâs degree in health / hospital management from recognised university with at least 5 years of hands-on experience in managing a hospital. Excellent communication, negotiation and analytical skills along with good MS Office application skills (Word, Excel, Power Point) are mandatory.
How to apply:
Candidates meeting the above criteria are invited to send their applications with CV to HR Department, Aga Khan Health Service, Pakistan-Regional Office, Alpine Complex, Vahadat Colony, Jutial-Gilgit or email with position applied in subject line at hr.gb@akhsp.org by May 11, 2014.
Only short-listed candidates will be contacted.
